@startuml contextDiagram
!theme plain

actor "Developer" as User

rectangle "VS Code" {
    component "Frank!Framework Extension" as Extension
}

rectangle "External Tools & Resources" {
    component "Frank!Runner\n(Git submodule)" as Runner
    component "Frank!Doc" as Documentation
    component "Frank!Framework Wiki" as Wiki
    component "Docker Compose" as Docker
    component "Apache Ant" as Ant
}

User -> Extension : Interacts with

Extension ..> Runner : Runs Frank projects via Ant
Extension ..> Docker : Runs Frank projects via Docker Compose
Extension ..> Ant : Executes Ant build scripts
Extension ..> Documentation : Links component docs (Frank!Doc)
Extension ..> Wiki : Fetches framework snippets

note right of Extension
  **Features:**
  * Create new Frank projects (Simple, Skeleton, etc.)
  * Run Frank via Ant or Docker Compose
  * Visualize configuration as flowchart (SVG)
  * Real-time XML validation (debounced 300ms)
  * Go-to-definition & Find References (pipes, sessionkeys)
  * Rename refactoring (pipe names, sessionkeys)
  * Manage & insert snippets (Wiki-sourced & user-created)
  * Frank!Doc hyperlinks in XML editor
end note

@enduml
